conclusion: Objects A and B are airborne and affected by gravity.
While airborne, A and B accelerate downward due to gravity.
A and B reach the level of the four fixed blocks C-D-E-F.
Object A makes first contact with the top faces of blocks C and D.
Object B makes first contact with the top faces of blocks E and F.
Normal force from the tops of the blocks balances the weight of A and B, bringing their downward motion to rest.
Provided tops of blocks are horizontal and centers of mass of A and B remain inside the area supported by the blocks, A and B come to rest on the block pairs.
No further motion occurs unless the set-up is uneven or the impact is off-center.
Final result: Objects A and B land on, and come to rest upon, the block pairs C-D and E-F respectively.
